          <h4 class="text-sm font-mono text-muted uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Clinical Explanation</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-ink leading-relaxed font-sans text-pretty">
            Your elevated <strong class="font-medium">TSH</strong> level (6.82) alongside normal <strong class="font-medium">Free T4</strong> indicates <strong class="text-primary font-medium">Subclinical Hypothyroidism</strong>. Your brain's pituitary gland is working slightly harder to signal your thyroid gland to produce hormones. This is a very common condition in India and is a frequent contributor to feelings of low energy, mild cold sensitivity, and difficulty in weight management.
